#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo Linux Installer LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:81
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A LiveCD is a bootable medium which contains a self-sustained Gentoo \n"
"environment. It allows you to boot Linux from the CD. During the boot process \n"
"your hardware is detected and the appropriate drivers are loaded. The Gentoo \n"
"Installation CDs are maintained by Gentoo developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "There currently are two Installation CDs available:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:93
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Installer LiveCD contains everything you need to install Gentoo. It\n"
"    provides a graphical environment, a graphical as well as console based\n"
"    installer which automatically carries out the installation for you, and of\n"
"    course, the installation instructions for your architecture.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Minimal Installation CD contains only a minimal environment that allows \n"
"    you to boot up and configure your network so you can connect to the \n"
"    Internet. It does not contain any additional files and cannot be used \n"
"    during the current installation approach.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download, Burn and Boot the Gentoo Linux Installer LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Burning the Installer LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can download the Installer LiveCDs from one of our <uri \n"
"link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri>. They are located in \n"
"the <path>releases/x86/2006.0/livecd</path> directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:123
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside that directory you'll find an ISO-file. That is a full CD image which\n"
"you can write on a CD-R.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:128
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After downloading the file, you can verify its integrity to see if it is \n"
"corrupted or not:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:134
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can check its MD5 checksum and compare it with the MD5 checksum we \n"
"    provide (for instance with the <c>md5sum</c> tool under Linux/Unix or \n"
"    <uri link=\"http://www.etree.org/md5com.html\">md5sum</uri> for Windows)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can verify the cryptographic signature that we provide. You need to\n"
"    obtain the public key we use (17072058) before you proceed though.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fetch our public key using the GnuPG application, run the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:148
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --keyserver subkeys.pgp.net --recv-keys 17072058</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now verify the signature:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify the cryptographic signature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --verify &lt;signature file&gt; &lt;downloaded iso&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:161
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To burn the downloaded ISO(s), you have to select raw-burning. How you\n"
"do this is highly program-dependent. We will discuss <c>cdrecord</c> and\n"
"<c>K3B</c> here; more information can be found in our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#isoburning\">Gentoo FAQ</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:169
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With cdrecord, you simply type <c>cdrecord dev=/dev/hdc &lt;downloaded iso\n"
"    file&gt;</c> (replace <path>/dev/hdc</path> with your CD-RW drive's device\n"
"    path).\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:174
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With K3B, select <c>Tools</c> &gt; <c>CD</c> &gt; <c>Burn Image</c>. Then\n"
"    you can locate your ISO file within the 'Image to Burn' area. Finally click\n"
"    <c>Start</c>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting the Installer LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><impo>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:187
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Read this whole subsection before continuing, as you will probably not have the\n"
"opportunity to read it before doing things later.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:192
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once you have burned your LiveCD, it is time to boot it. Remove all CDs from\n"
"your CD drives, reboot your system and enter the BIOS.  This is usually done by\n"
"hitting DEL, F1 or ESC, depending on your BIOS. Inside  the BIOS, change the\n"
"boot order so that the CD-ROM is tried before the hard disk. This is often found\n"
"under \"CMOS Setup\". If you don't do this, your system will just reboot from the\n"
"hard disk, ignoring the CD-ROM.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:201
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now place the LiveCD in the CD-ROM drive and reboot. You should see a boot\n"
"prompt. At this screen, you can hit Enter to begin the boot process with the\n"
"default boot options, or boot the LiveCD with custom boot options by specifying\n"
"a kernel followed by boot options and then hitting Enter.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:208
#, no-wrap
