msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:426
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extra Hardware Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:430
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When the LiveCD boots, it tries to detect all your hardware devices and\n"
"loads the appropriate kernel modules to support your hardware. In the\n"
"vast majority of cases, it does a very good job. However, in some cases, it \n"
"may not auto-load the kernel modules you need. If the PCI auto-detection \n"
"missed some of your system's hardware, you will have to load the appropriate\n"
"kernel modules manually. These tasks require root access.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:439
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the next example we try to load the <c>8139too</c> module (support for \n"
"certain kinds of network interfaces):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:443
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading kernel modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:444
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>modprobe 8139too</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:448
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you need PCMCIA support, you should start the <c>pcmcia</c> init script:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:451
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting the PCMCIA init script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:452
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/etc/init.d/pcmcia start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:458
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Tweaking Hard Disk Performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are an advanced user, you might want to tweak the IDE hard disk\n"
"performance using <c>hdparm</c>. You will need root access to use <c>hdparm</c>.\n"
"With the <c>-tT</c> options you can test the performance of your disk (execute\n"
"it several times to get a more precise impression):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:468
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:469
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>hdparm -tT /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:473
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To tweak, you can use any of the following examples (or experiment\n"
"yourself) which use <path>/dev/hda</path> as disk (substitute with your\n"
"disk):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:478
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tweaking hard disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:479
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>Activate DMA:</comment>                       # <i>hdparm -d 1 /dev/hda</i>\n"
"<comment>Activate Safe Performance Options:</comment>  # <i>hdparm -d 1 -A 1 -m 16 -u 1 -a 64 /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:486
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: User Accounts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:490
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you plan on giving other people access to your installation\n"
"environment or you want to chat using <c>irssi</c> without root privileges (for\n"
"security reasons), you need to create the necessary user accounts and change \n"
"the root password. You need root access to change the root password and add new\n"
"users.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:498
#, no-wrap
msgid "To change the root password, use the <c>passwd</c> utility:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:501
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:502
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>sudo su -</i>\n"
"# <i>passwd</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter your new password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter your password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:509
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To create a user account, we first enter their credentials, followed by\n"
"its password. We use <c>useradd</c> and <c>passwd</c> for these tasks.\n"
"In the next example, we create a user called &quot;john&quot;.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:514
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a user account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:515
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>useradd -m -G users john</i>\n"
"# <i>passwd john</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter john's password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter john's password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:522
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can change your user id from root to the newly created user by using\n"
"<c>su</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:526
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing user id"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:527
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>su - john</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:531
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can also change the password for the \"gentoo\" user in the graphical\n"
"environment. This account is already suitable for use on the Internet.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:535
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the gentoo password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:536
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>passwd</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter your new password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter your password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:545
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Viewing Documentation while Installing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:549
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to view the Gentoo Handbook (either from-CD or online) during the\n"
"installation, make sure you have created a user account (see <uri\n"
"link=\"#useraccounts\">Optional: User Accounts</uri>). Then press <c>Alt-F2</c> to\n"
"go to a new terminal and log in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:556
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to view the documentation on the CD you can immediately run\n"
"<c>links</c> to read it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:560
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the on-CD documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:561
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>links /mnt/cdrom/docs/handbook/html/index.html</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:565
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"However, it is preferred that you use the online Gentoo Handbook as it will be\n"
"more recent than the one provided on the CD. You can view it using <c>links</c>\n"
"as well, but only after having completed the <e>Configuring your Network</e>\n"
"chapter (otherwise you won't be able to go on the Internet to view the\n"
"document):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:572
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the Online Documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:573
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>links http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:577
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can go back to your original window by pressing <c>Alt-F7</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2006.0/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:581
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can now choose to proceed by using the <uri link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=3\">GTK+\n"
"based installer</uri> (which needs X) or the <uri\n"
"link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=4\">Dialog based installer</uri> that can be run on a\n"
"console.\n"
msgstr ""
